						               													<description>You&amp;rsquo;re a cat now! And as any self-respecting cat, your way of life is to make as much mischief as possible. But beware : don't get caught by a Hooman or you&amp;rsquo;ll be grounded! Try to blame another cat instead!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player plays his turn, starting by the first player. You can make 3 different moves:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1.    Play a hidden card in front of you&amp;#10;2.    Play a hidden card in front of another player&amp;#10;3.    Draw one to two cards from the deck&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When everybody has made a move, all players reveal the cards and effects are applied on the shared mischief stair. Then check who got caught!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the game, there are 3 kinds of cards:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Mischief: Increase the Hooman owner awareness and anger&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Purring: lower the Hooman owner awareness and anger&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Sneaky: Increase the Hooman owner awareness and anger but change the tide of a turn!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a cat was very bad and grounded 20 times or when the deck is empty. The less grounded cat wins the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cat&amp;rsquo;astrophes is a family card game for 2 to 6 players. &amp;#10;Recommended starting age is 7+. Play session lasts about 15 minutes on average. Both core board gamers and casual players can enjoy the game due to the guessing mechanic and the possibility to use strategies!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
